<br>
 That's one market. Quick turnaround of the vehicle definitely pays off here, since the price for a few minutes above the atmosphere in zeroG could come down.<br>
<br>
 Another thing many X-Prize designs point to is global rapid transport. If the vehicle can carry the equivalent of 3 people to sub-orbital hops, then it can toss an upper stage higher. Either a micro-satellite into LEO, or a larger payload across the planet.<br>
 Governments will go berserk if this kind of capability gets widespread, since guided re-entry missiles would be cheap &amp; simple. That's one market, if you want to call it that.<br>
 Package delivery companies have already stated that there's most definitely a market for this kind of transport. Nobody knows the shape of the system -parachute the parcel into an empty field?<br>
<br>
Could a passenger be squeexed into an upper stage payload reentry module of an X-Prize vehicle? Probably not the first generation version. Build it up to a few tons suborbital. No orbital circularizing on the upper stage would mean landing capability of a passenger pod.<br>
 Quite a ride! You mean people would have to pay to ride it? Which way would the money flow for this kind of a ride?<br>
<br>
Anybody ever read about Gagarin's ride? He had basically no controls. No RCS whatsoever on his pod. The craft fired the de-orbit motors, after which the crew pod separated.<br>
 The balancing of the crew pod was the only stabilization used: the weight of the man made it settle down as it entered the upper atmosphere. After it slowed down, the 'chutes came out.<br>
 At low altitude, he rode an ejection seat out of the pod, and landed like any other pilot who's bailed out!<br>
<br>
 A bit rough for a paid passenger or even a high-priced adenture ride! They'll have to smoothe out the bumps first. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=332.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <br><br><a self href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=332.topic&index=19><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/addreply3.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=332.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.threadControl?topicID=332.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/space/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=332.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=332.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub97.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select n